ge 2015 form 10-k 208
derivatives and hedging
note 20 provides the primary information related to our derivatives and hedging activity. this section provides certain supplemental information about this topic.
as described in note 20, changes in the fair value of derivatives are recorded in a separate component of equity (referred to below as accumulated other comprehensive income, or aoci) and are recorded in earnings in the period in which the hedged transaction occurs. the table below summarizes this activity by hedging instrument.
