derivatives are classified in the captions "all other assets" and "all other liabilities" and the related accrued interest is classified in "other ge capital receivables" and "all other liabilities" in our financial statements.
(a) the netting of derivative receivables and payables is permitted when a legally enforceable master netting agreement exists. amounts include fair value adjustments related to our own and counterparty non-performance risk. at december 31, 2015 and 2014, the cumulative adjustment for non-performance risk was insignificant and $16 million, respectively.
(b) excluded excess cash collateral received and posted of $48 million and $379 million at december 31, 2015, respectively, and $63 million and $195 million at december 31, 2014, respectively.
(c) excluded excess securities collateral received of $107 million and $471 million at december 31, 2015 and 2014, respectively.
